cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SI, cs.DS

This paper deals with natural language processing and computational linguistics, specifically the analysis of relative clauses in English and Dutch using vector-based models. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also uses algebraic structures and extended versions of Lambek calculus, which are related to machine learning and artificial intelligence, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) likely sub-categories as well. The paper also involves mathematical analysis and modeling, which could fall under cs.SI (Signal and Image Processing) or cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
